Bootstrap: localimage
From: ../test.sif

%files
    ./config.py /Test_setChr8_Evaluator/config.py
    ./data_loader.py /Test_setChr8_Evaluator/data_loader.py
    ./evaluator_content_handler.py /Test_setChr8_Evaluator/evaluator_content_handler.py 
    ./evaluator_metrics_calculator.py /Test_setChr8_Evaluator/evaluator_metrics_calculator.py
    ./evaluator_RestAPI.py /Test_setChr8_Evaluator/evaluator_RestAPI.py

%environment
    # Prevent automatic binding of host directories
    export APPTAINER_NO_MOUNT="home,tmp,proc,sys,dev"

%post
    # The base's default python is orca_env; make that explicit so the pip below
    # installs into orca_env and not the system python:3.13-slim interpreter.
    export PATH="/opt/conda/envs/orca_env/bin:$PATH"

    echo "Installing evaluator client dependencies into orca_env..."
    # requests + msgpack(+numpy) are what the evaluator actually uses; seqstr/torch
    # /scipy/pandas/numpy/orca_predict are already in the base. flask is unused by
    # the evaluator (client side) but kept for parity with the prod build.
    pip install flask msgpack msgpack_numpy requests

    echo "Setting permissions..."
    chmod -R 755 /Test_setChr8_Evaluator

%runscript
    export PATH="/opt/conda/envs/orca_env/bin:$PATH"
    exec python /Test_setChr8_Evaluator/evaluator_RestAPI.py "$@"

%startscript
    export PATH="/opt/conda/envs/orca_env/bin:$PATH"
    exec python /Test_setChr8_Evaluator/evaluator_RestAPI.py "$@"

%labels
    Author "Rui Guo with edits from Ishika Luthra and Satyam Priyadarshi"
    game_schema_version "1.0"
    Description "This container is the Test Set Chr8 Evaluator set up using the Genomic API for Model Evaluation framework."

%help
    Test Set Chr8 Evaluator for the GAME framework (ORCA 1M Predictor).

    About this evaluator:
    Tiles human chromosome 8 (GRCh38, the ORCA held-out test set) into 1 Mb windows,
    fetches each hg38 sequence at runtime, and requests interaction_matrix predictions of 3D 
    chromatin conformation. Each predicted 250x250 H1-ESC contact matrix is compared against
    the measured Hi-C target via Pearson r, enabling standardized evaluation of genomic 
    models on chromatin conformation.

    This container includes:
    - Evaluator API script for genomic sequence evaluation
    - Evaluator utility scripts (data loading, content negotiation, metrics calculation)
    - Installed Python dependencies required by the Evaluator

    Built on the Orca eval base (test.sif): orca_env, CUDA 11.8 torch, seqstr,
    and the resources_core + resources_mcools target data under /orca/resources.

    Mount the data and output directories at runtime:
        apptainer run --nv \
            -B /path/to/Test_setChr8_Evaluator/evaluator_data:/evaluator_data \
            -B /path/to/predictions:/predictions \
            orca-testSet-chr8_evaluator.sif <predictor_ip> <predictor_port> /predictions

    - `--nv` exposes the host GPU (the evaluator recomputes Hi-C targets via Orca)
    - `/evaluator_data` must contain `chr8_sequence_coordinates.json`
    - The third argument is the in-container output path (the mount target above).

    